The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 Some former Mohun Bagan players, including Subrata Bhattacharjee, Manas Bhattacharjee and Goutam Sarkar, have decided to skip the Mohun Bagan Day celebrations on July 29. Accusing the Bagan management of improper treatment, the ex-players after an hour-long meeting at a city hotel on Monday decided instead to distribute footballs, jerseys and football-shoes among district football academies to mark the occasion.           
	 Mohun Bagan Monday signed four players  Marcos Pereira, Ishfaq Ahmed, Anand Vasan, who were retained and, Santa Kumar from Pune FC  for the ensuing season. While Chirag United signed 15 players. George Telegraph had nine players signing for them.                
	GOLF: The Telegraph Cup at the RCGC from 7am                                                                                                                                                                       
